[Student "S"]
{SOUTH jumps to 4\S, confident that NORTH could make 10 tricks 
even if he just has 6 points.

NORTH knows he can make more and bids RKCB 4NT.

SOUTH's 5\D response shows zero or three Keycards. 
So which is it? Zero or three?

SOUTH bid much too strongly to have no Aces. NORTH 
bids a confident 6\S, knowing SOUTH has either three Aces or two Aces plus the \SK.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:6.AK9754.6.KQJT3 QT842.2.QJ73.874 A75.QT83.A854.92 KJ93.J6.KT92.A65"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6H"]
